<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-10-16T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-10-16T09:00:00-05:00" n="594" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d594">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">638.5131/182: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Finley</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Port-au-Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-10-16T09:00:00-05:00">October 16, 1937—9
                                a.m.</date><lb/>[Received 9:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>91. Haitian Government has just informed me that on October 11 it
                            instructed Chatelain to advise the Quai D’Orsay that Haiti would be
                            willing to conclude the proposed commercial convention with France if it
                            can be granted a quota of 100,000 instead of 120,000 quintals of
                            coffee.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Finley</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>